The White House Press Secretary congratulates Ma Ying-jeou on his reelection as President of Taiwan and commends the people of Taiwan for the successful conduct of their presidential and legislative elections. Taiwan's economic and political development over the past decades has made it a success story in Asia. The elections have once again demonstrated the strength and vitality of Taiwan's democratic system. The United States is confident that Taiwan will continue to build on its accomplishments, and both countries will work together to advance their common interests, including expanding trade and investment ties. The United States emphasizes the importance of peace, stability, and improved relations between Taiwan and China, free from intimidation. The relationship between the United States and Taiwan is based on common interests and a shared commitment to freedom and democracy. The United States will continue to maintain its close unofficial ties with Taiwan through the American Institute in Taiwan, in accordance with its one China policy based on the three Joint Communiqu√©s with China and the Taiwan Relations Act.